<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,760,1534,2069]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1566,1589]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Comment.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber, 1858" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1858" box="[405,679,1566,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,530,1566,1589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Hallodapus</emphasis>
Fieber, 1858
</taxonomicName>
is represented by two species in 
<collectingCountry box="[462,544,1598,1621]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herrich-Schaffer, 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1839" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis box="[558,691,1598,1621]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">H. suturalis</emphasis>
(Herrich-Schäffer, 1839)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnavuori, 1984)" baseAuthorityName="Linnavuori" baseAuthorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoconcolor">
<emphasis box="[417,619,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">H. pseudoconcolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E." pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref9262" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. 1984: New species of Hemiptera Heteroptera from Iraq and the adjacent countries. Acta Entomologica Fennica 44: 1 - 59." type="journal article" year="1984">Linnavuori, 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. While the former is widely distributed in the West Palaearctic 
<collectingRegion box="[274,354,1694,1717]" country="Iraq" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Region</collectingRegion>
, the latter is only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[673,716,1694,1717]" name="Iraq" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Iraq</collectingCountry>
and the South East of 
<collectingCountry box="[343,419,1726,1749]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MATOCQ A. &amp; PLUOT-SIGWALT D. &amp; OZGEN I." box="[433,645,1726,1749]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="884 - 930" refId="ref9776" refString="MATOCQ A., PLUOT-SIGWALT D. &amp; OZGEN I. 2014: Terrestrial Hemiptera (Heteroptera) collected in South-East Anatolia (Diyarbakir, Mardin and Elazig provinces) (Turkey): second list. Munis Entomology and Zoology 9: 884 - 930." type="journal article" year="2014">MATOCQ et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter, 1890" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Hallodapus concolor</emphasis>
Reuter, 1890
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in tropical Africa from 
<collectingCountry box="[210,321,1790,1813]" name="Cameroon" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[357,424,1790,1813]" name="Sudan" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and in Asia from 
<collectingCountry box="[620,760,1790,1813]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,316,1822,1845]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
all the way to 
<collectingCountry box="[492,593,1822,1845]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Kirghizia</collectingCountry>
and in Europe only in 
<collectingRegion box="[234,292,1854,1877]" country="Greece" name="Kriti" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Crete</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[307,386,1854,1877]" name="Greece" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Greece</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="KERZHNER I. M. &amp; JOSIFOV M." box="[408,693,1854,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 576" refId="ref9051" refString="KERZHNER I. M. &amp; JOSIFOV M. 1999: Miridae Hahn, 1833. Pp: 1 - 576. In: AUKEMA B. &amp; RIEGER C. (eds.): Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 1, Enicocephalomorpha, Dipsocoromorpha, Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha and Leptopodomorpha. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, xiv + 577 pp." type="book chapter" year="1999">KERZHNER &amp; JOSIFOV 1999</bibRefCitation>
). This species was observed to live on low grass vegetation in dry sandy areas (
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E." box="[331,515,1918,1941]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref9399" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. 1996: Miridae of West and Central Africa (Hemiptera, Heteroptera). Acta Zoologica Fennica 202: 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="1996">LINNAVUORI 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1890" box="[534,760,1918,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concolor">
<emphasis box="[534,760,1918,1941]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">Hallodapus concolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 8A, B) is most similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnavuori" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[508,715,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoconcolor">
<emphasis box="[508,715,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="301">H. pseudoconcolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it in the shape of the left paramere and theca (see 
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E." box="[201,385,2014,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref9262" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. 1984: New species of Hemiptera Heteroptera from Iraq and the adjacent countries. Acta Entomologica Fennica 44: 1 - 59." type="journal article" year="1984">LINNAVUORI 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
